  "pages": [
    {
      "type": "patchouli:text",
      "text": "So, you've reached the Iron Age and you want an upgrade? Well, the rowboat is for you. It has three seats, so it can hold 3 players, or up to 2 animals, including horses! As always, you can also replace seats (except for the pilot seat) with containers of your choosing. You can also place two additional containers at the stern."
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:image",
      "images": [
        "firmaciv:textures/gui/book/rowboat_isometric.png"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:text",
      "text": "In the rowboat, unlike other boats, you'll be sitting backwards when you're piloting the boat. It gives you a mechanical advantage so you can really put your back into those oars! You can, of course, pilot it in first-person, but if you may find it more intuitive in third-person facing yourself."
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:crafting",
      "recipe": "firmaciv:crafting/watercraft_frame_angled",
      "text": "To build a rowboat, you'll need to start with Shipwright's Scaffolding. These allow you to keep the boat materials in place while you build. $(br2)Then, you'll place them facing inward in a 2 by 3 area."
    },
